    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-03T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="116"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5074</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Droppers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-03T16:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 4, 1 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>345. British Minister informs me British forces are to be withdrawn from
                    Macedonia owing to difficulty of provisioning by sea. This will probably mean
                    evacuation Monastir territory. Other reasons also suspected, not disclosed,
                    possibly arrangements with Bulgarians.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Droppers</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
